  "text": "The biological stimuli of paracrine and autocrine origin constitute a complex network in the bone metastasis microenvironment, important for dictating the various phases of colonization. Additionally, there is evidence of the interaction between biological and physical (hypoxia) stimuli in the transdifferentiation programs EMT and the reverse MET (epithelial phenotype) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
